gomodel:SYNGO_2719  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Golgi-associated JNK3 mediates stress-induced reduction of surface AMPAR\"\n- \"Given that the palmitoylation of JNK3 in primary neurons was increased after NMDA treatment (Fig. 1F), we investigated whether JNK3 inhibited stress-induced secretory trafficking in neurons by monitoring the trafficking of AMPAR GluR1 in response to NMDA-induced neuronal stress\"\n- \"A significant and gradual reduction of surface, but not total, GluR1 was detected in rat hippocampal or cortical neurons challenged with NMDA despite the presence of the JNK inhibitors SP600125 or NIMoE (Fig. 2C and fig. S6, B and C). This reduction of surface GluR1 was mostly prevented by short hairpin RNA (shRNA)-mediated knockdown of endogenous JNK3 (Fig. 2D), which could be reversed by overexpressing the shRNA-resistant kinase-deficient JNK3 mutant (JNK3 KD) but not the kinase-deficient JNK3 KD-CS mutant, which cannot be palmitoylated (Fig. 2E).\"\n\n23/2/2018 PIm\n- The application of NMDA places this data in synaptic context.. Experimental description: From \"MATERIALS AND METHODS\"\nCell culture and materials: ...Primary cortical or hippocampal neuronal\ncultures were prepared from Wistar rat (University of British Columbia\nAnimal Care Centre) brains at embryonic days 18 to 19...\nThe GFP-tagged GluR1 wild-type and the C585S mutant constructs were a gift from\nR. Huganir. The constructs expressing FLAG-JNK1, FLAG-JNK2, FLAG-JNK3,\nBDNF-GFP, and VSVGts045-CFP (cyan fluorescent protein) were\npurchased from Addgene. The expression construct of rat Sac1 was purchased\nfrom OriGene...." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2719" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

